        <h2>What is Diabetes?</h2>
        <p>Diabetes is a medical condition where the body cannot maintain healthy blood glucose levels.
            <br><b>Insulin</b> is the hormone enabling the body to properly break down sugars in food; a
            diabetic is unable to adequately produce insulin, or produce any insulin at all. <br>This can
            lead to serious health complications if not properly treated. Diabetes technology has seen much
            innovation in recent years, enabling more effective diabetes management. For more information on
            new diabetes technology, click <a
                href="https://www.diabetesaustralia.com.au/living-with-diabetes/managing-your-diabetes/diabetes-technology/">here.</a>
        </p>
