            <div class="accordian-content">
                <p><b>Type 1 diabetes</b> accounts for approximately 10 percent of all diabetes cases. It is an
                    auto-immune condition with unknown causes, although there is a strong genetic link. It
                    cannot be prevented or cured, but it can be managed effectively, leading to a healthy
                    life with few complications. Type 1 diabetes management involves multiple daily insulin
                    injections and regular blood glucose monitoring.
                    For more information on Type 1 diabetes, see: <a
                        href="https://www.diabetesaustralia.com.au/about-diabetes/type-1-diabetes/">Type 1
                        Diabetes Information.</a>
                </p>
