            <div class="accordian-content">
                <p><b>Type 2 diabetes</b> accounts for approximately 85 percent of all diabetes cases. Type 2
                    diabetes is caused by a gradual buildup of insulin resistance in the body. Long term
                    lifestyle choices, such as dietary and exercise habits, have a significant effect on
                    the development of Type 2 diabetes. Genetic and ethnic factors are also significant.
                    Type 2 diabetes can lead to significant health complications if unchecked, but can
                    be managed through healthy eating, regular exercise, and in some cases tablets or
                    insulin.
                    For more information on Type 2 diabetes, see: <a
                        href="https://www.diabetesaustralia.com.au/about-diabetes/type-2-diabetes/">Type
